cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.AR, cs.DC, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 

1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper primarily deals with the design and implementation of an Ethernet-based mobile fronthaul network, which involves various networking and internet architecture concepts. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the delay and jitter requirements of CPRI over Ethernet, which are related to information theory concepts such as channel capacity and error correction. 
3. cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) - The paper uses FPGA-based Verilog experiments and simulations to evaluate the performance of CoE, which involves hardware architecture design and implementation. 
4. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper discusses the scheduling policy of CoE flows on Ethernet, which is related to distributed computing concepts such as load balancing and resource allocation. 
5. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - The paper discusses the reconfigurability of Ethernet-based mobile fronthaul networks, which involves software engineering concepts such as software-defined networking and network function virtualization.
